Django + virtualenv Basic commands:

-->
If you are using virtualenv then,
-->
__
To make new virtual environment:
1. to create in current directory
`virtualenv .`

or
2. to create virtua env in separate directory
virtaulenv /home/bittu/Desktop/trialProject

3. to create virtual env with python 3
virtaulenv /home/bittu/Desktop/trialProject -p python3
__
To activate virtual enve using terminal
`source bin/activate`

__
To deactivate virtual enve using terminal
`deactivate`

-->
Install/Create the dependencies
-->
__
To create a requirement list
`pip freeze > requirements.txt`

__
To install dependencies
`pip install -r requirements.txt`


-->
Django
-->
__
Start Django Project
`django-admin startproject __$name_of_the_project__`

__
Create Database (or create migration for the database)
`python manage.py makemigrations`

__
Migrate Database (to start database -- create database entries)
`python manage.py migrate`

__
Create web app
`python manage.py startapp __$name_of_the_app__"

__
Run Server
`python manage.py runserver`

__
Create superuser(create admin user)
`python manage.py createsuperuser`

__
Access python and django project from shell
`python manage.py shell`
Example. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ACdY7pId4DM&index=13&list=PLEsfXFp6DpzQSEMN5PXvEWuD2gEWVngCZ

__
after updating models.py
always run,
`python manage.py makemigrations`
`python manage.py migrate`
